{"id":"12743","name":"Connection Control","tagline":"Integration for automations to change and revert network connections.","icon":"ios15 c946986751 g59867","latest":"34441","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Write down any of the following commands in any order, separated by a new line in a text block. Use the text block as input for the shortcut.</p>\n<p>———————</p>\n<p>Record - Writes the current state of wifi/cellular/airplane mode to a file in the shortcuts folder.</p>\n<p>Connect - Activates wifi and cellular and then runs the Await* command.</p>\n<p>Await* - Waits for an internet connection.</p>\n<p>Disconnect - Switches on airplane mode and turn off wifi.</p>\n<p>Revert - Reverts to the state registered using the record command.</p>\n<p>——————</p>\n<p>*Requires Toolbox Pro</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0 - Aug. 4, 2022, 10:40 p.m.</strong></p><p>* Integrates UpdateKit 2.0 and later.<br>* Changes some phrasings in the documentation.<br><br>Tested on iOS 16 beta 4</p>"}